      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the tangzhong",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whisk together the {{strong-bread-flour}} (tangzhong amount) and {{whole-milk}} (tangzhong amount) in a small saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture thickens to a smooth, gelatinous paste that pulls away from the sides of the pan, about 3 to 4 minutes. Scrape into a bowl and cool to room temperature.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the dough and bulk ferment, 90 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the {{strong-bread-flour}} (dough amount), {{caster-sugar}}, {{sea-salt-fine}}, and {{yeast-dried}} in a large bowl. Add the cooled tangzhong, {{whole-milk}} (dough amount), and {{eggs}} (one). Mix to a rough dough, then knead for 10 minutes. Add the softened {{unsalted-butter}} piece by piece and knead for a further 8 minutes until smooth and elastic. Cover and leave for 90 minutes until doubled.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape, proof, and bake, 30 to 35 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Divide the dough into four equal pieces. Flatten each, roll into a rough rectangle, then roll up into a cylinder. Place side by side in a greased 900 g loaf tin. Cover and prove for 60 minutes until the dough has risen to the rim of the tin. Brush with beaten egg. Bake at 180°C fan for 30 to 35 minutes, until deep amber and the base sounds hollow when tapped. Cool on a rack for at least 1 hour before slicing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
